          "text": "There's significant chatter on X about OpenAI's products, particularly a backlash against the planned deprecation of GPT-4o (and related models like GPT-4.1) from ChatGPT's app and web platforms on February 13, 2026.[[1]](https://x.com/i/status/2018344258294497575)[[2]](https://x.com/i/status/2018500813270970515)[[3]](https://x.com/i/status/2018731457418858940)[[4]](https://x.com/i/status/2018942459468787995)[[5]](https://x.com/i/status/2018633348835356741) Users under hashtags like #keep4o and #keep4oAPI argue it's a \"bait and switch,\" highlighting emotional attachments (e.g., ~70% non-work usage for companionship), potential legal issues tied to Senator Warren's financial inquiry deadline on the same date, and calls for legacy access for paying subscribers.[[6]](https://x.com/i/status/2018641045777793032)[[7]](https://x.com/i/status/2018600484047569402)\n\nOther highlights:\n- Anthropic is running Super Bowl ads mocking ChatGPT's new ads, pledging no ads in Claude.[[8]](https://x.com/i/status/2019039874771550516)\n- ChatGPT handles ~1 million local news queries weekly.[[9]](https://x.com/i/status/2019116499382714701)\n- Tips for building ChatGPT apps shared on OpenAI's dev blog.[[10]](https://x.com/i/status/2019079610990800998)\n\nLess mention of GPT-5 (one post references a forced \"gpt-5.2\" shift), OpenAI API, ChatGPT broadly, or o1 specifically in top results.[[4]](https://x.com/i/status/2018942459468787995)",
